    "Dapper and cultured, McComb conducted several love affairs without concealment.": [],
    "In 1939 McComb was denied tenured at Harvard, partly due, according Freedberg, to a reticence to ingratiate himself with powerful Harvard faculty such as <a href=\"/sachsp\">Paul J. Sachs</a> and his public philandering.": [
